 three orders of magnitude lower compared to the observed rate, of\norder $10^{-3} \\, \\mathrm{M}_\\odot^{-1}$. The low rates can be ascribed to\ninteractions before the stars evolve to CO WDs. However, our results are lower\nlimits given that we considered a subset of quadruple systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Apr 2018 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-02"}
