once $g\\gg 1$, though this is surely\nknown to experts (the difference is the use of the Kabatiansky-Levenshtein\nbound in lieu of more elementary techniques).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Apr 2018 18:00:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-18"}
